.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.RI [ command ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
program provides a command line interface that allows the user to execute UNIX commands.
It mimics basic functionalities of standard shells such as
.BR sh (1)
and
.BR bash (1),
including:

.IP \[bu] 2
Displaying a prompt and waiting for user input.
.IP \[bu] 2
Executing commands with arguments.
.IP \[bu] 2
Searching for executables in the
.BR PATH .
.IP \[bu] 2
Handling built-in commands such as
.BR exit
and
.BR env .

.SH TASKS AND EXAMPLES

.SS 0.1 \- Basic Shell
Display a prompt, read input, and execute simple one-word commands.

.EX
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
README.md  main.h  main.c
($)
.EE

.SS 0.2 \- Handle PATH
Allow commands without full paths. The shell searches each directory in the PATH variable.
If the command does not exist, it prints an error and does not call fork().

.EX
$ ./hsh
($) ls
README.md  main.c  main.h
($) fakecommand
./hsh: 1: fakecommand: not found
($)
.EE

.SS 0.3 \- Exit Built-in
Implement the built-in command
.B exit
that terminates the shell.

.EX
$ ./hsh
($) ls
main.c  run.c
($) exit
$
.EE

.SS 0.4 \- Env Built-in
Implement the built-in command
.B env
that prints the current environment variables.

.EX
$ ./hsh
($) env
USER=julien
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
HOME=/home/julien
($)
.EE

.SH RETURN VALUE
The exit status of
.B simple_shell
is the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B main.h
Header file containing all function prototypes and macros.
.TP
.B main.c
Main loop of the shell.
.TP
.B run.c
Handles execution of commands and built-ins.
.TP
.B path.c
Searches for commands in the PATH directories.
.TP
.B parse_input.c
Splits user input into tokens.
.TP
.B free_args.c
Frees dynamically allocated argument arrays.

